{"key":"post-7350831","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7350831</id>\n<content>Never heat a terrarium.  The temperature differential will 'steal' your humidity in order to turn it into condensation on the walls-bad idea.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You want upper ninety percent humidity inside your terrarium.  Rinsed and well drained perlite is an excellent way to get this.  Use a small heater in the room to get the temps to upper sixties-low seventies and you'll be fine.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7369444</next>\n<prev>7350596</prev>\n<first>7334981</first>\n<last>7369486</last>\n<when>1188478159</when>\n<utime>08/30/07 03:49 PM</utime>\n</post>"}